Category:  General  Topic:  look



This command shows you all in your immediate room, all that you can detect
easily that is.  You can also look at specific objects, people, and doors
for more detailed descriptions of each.  Note that some things exist in a
room, but may be impossible to see if you don't know exactly what to look
for (ie it's name).

Syntax:  look <i_th> [object]

Example:  look		shows current room
	  look guard	shows you the guard

See Also:  examine, brief, read
